data.jamchart_notes: Melodic first jam gives way to a cowbell-driven, spacey jam. Trevor and Rick trade counterpoints until Trevor's soaring bass lines propel them to a beautiful peak! Not content, the band digs into a dirty groove to bring it home.

Monster AIN w/ multiple amazing movements. Pete opens things with incredible synth work, but Spuds is the real star; driving this monster jam towards a magnificent melodic peak! Some very funky playing from Richk closes this all-timer.
High energy, relentless jam that never lets up and ends in a mammoth shredfest peak.

data.jamchart_notes: A twisting “fast Need” with a danceable exploratory initial jam that pivots over a drum break into a more dynamic guitar-led section. Rick finds a new melody that the band quickly backs as a looping hook that naturally summons the composed tail.

data.jamchart_notes: Relentless and long first jam seamlessly transitions between major and minor key. Short second jam sees Peter doing some sparse organ leading before landing in "California Magic".

This truly elite “All I Need” is dark Goose jamming at its finest. Trevor-forward full band interplay with Spuds mimicking a violent half-speed thrash metal death march creates space for Rick to swirl brain-breaking minor-key runs over a bed of extra-terrestrial synths. If aliens ever attack, they’ll come blaring a six-minute loop of this jam on repeat from their flying saucer Alpines. The accidental second jam features some fine clav-work from Peter and an extended moody intro to “Nights in White Satin”.

data.jamchart_notes: Right out of the gate, the band dives into some Winter '22-style dark jamming. Peter goes to a haunting upright piano tone as he and Rick lock in. Spuds shoots the improv into a swirling vortex that transitions cleanly into some bluesy rock at Rick's urging. Organ and guitar trade riffs before Rick steers the band into three-chord bliss. Trevor really steps out on the sustained full-band peak w/ envelope filter work as the joyous peak wraps back to "AIN" proper and a second jam fakeout into "Dr. D."

data.jamchart_notes: First big "AIN" in almost a year sees some beautiful dynamic play from Rick as the band builds from quiet to a melodic peak. The final few minutes, however, are the real star with some contemplative, conversational work as the band works their way > to "Borne."

Kicking off with all the sonic flair of an Echo & The Bunnymen jamband equivalent, this show-highlight "All I Need" ventures through a highly satisfying section of the sort of low-calorie breezy propulsive bliss jamming that Goose makes look so effortless in 2025. Gorgeous stuff, making for contagious ear-to-ear grins right up through the transition -> "SALT".
